The swimming pool was closed for repair, but hey, we had the sea!	The amenities are limited and cheap (no soap for the shower?).	The room was an unusual shape but an acceptable size.	The one we got with the double bed was a little older, bathroom was not as updated as the others but still clean.	The minibar had decent prices for that, and the wireless internet was free.	The breakfast looked very good - but not worth 17 euros so we opted to go elsewhere.	The staff was fairly friendly and called a taxi for us when we departed the next day for the pier.